description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KADOORIE CENTRE FOR CRITICAL CARE RESEARCH AND EDUCATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOHN RADCLIFFE HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trauma Research Nurse or Research Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term, one year, full time (but part time will be considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers an ideal opportunity for a motivated, enthusiastic registered nurse or allied health professional who wishes to undertake clinical research. We are looking for an individual to join the trauma research team within the Kadoorie Centre for Critical Care Research and Education. We work closely with the Oxford Trauma Unit, Oxford University and the National Institute of Health Research, Clinical Research Network: Thames Valley and South Midlands and provide facilities for the conduct of clinical trials and research studies in a number of areas within trauma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the day-to-day management and co-ordination of clinical trials and research studies within the trial portfolio, ensuring they are conducted to the highest standard according to Good Clinical Practice guidelines. You will also contribute to the development and preparation of new clinical trials and research studies suitable for the United Kingdom Clinical Research Network (UKCRN) portfolio and raise the profile of clinical trials and research studies within the Trauma Unit, the Oxford University Hospitals Trust and throughout the Thames Valley. You will work collaboratively with the other members of the research team and with the wider multi-disciplinary community in the management of participants in research studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a valid professional registration and please identify how you meet the selection criteria and any transferrable skills in your application.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 22/11/20&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Liz Tutton - Senior Research Fellow, liz.tutton@ouh.nhs.uk, 01864 223106&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
